{
  "stem": "490.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I'm David Shear.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Previous, David Sukaczer.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I'm-- I was born September 17, in 1919.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in Poland.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was the Polish Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the name of the city was Luboml.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In Yiddish, Libivne.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You mean, before the war?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was a long stretch from Libivne to where the-- I met the-- the Germans.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I left Libivne when I was a youngster, when I finished my preliminary schooling.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so I left for the big city, to go to high school or further education.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And through-- I ended up-- from one city to another, from one school to another.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I ended up to be in central Poland, in Ostrowiec.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Ostrowca was a [BACKGROUND NOISE] different city than Luboml was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Luboml was more of the Russian-style Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Ostrowca was a Hasidic city, where the Jews were wearing long caftans and beards, and the-- the style of the Jewishness was different than the Ukrainian Jews.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I came to Ostrowca, which it was in 1935, I-- I came there because the-- the school-- at the time, they were called the yeshiva-- sent me.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When you graduated one school, they send you to a higher school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were all under the same name.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like it was the same type of schooling.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my type of yeshiva was-- it was more of a-- [NON-ENGLISH] built on-- based on Musar.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We did not-- our education was not to become a professional.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was to stay in the educated-- in the educational business, [BACKGROUND NOISE] whatever today you would call it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But at the time, it was to dedicate your life for Jewish culture and to continue living-- to continue to spread the Jewish culture.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I stayed in this-- in this yeshiva from '35.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
